# scripts/bench/guest.env — SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for the perf guest.
#
# Source this (never re-derive these values inline):  . scripts/bench/guest.env
# It is plain `KEY=value` POSIX sh — no side effects, safe to source repeatedly.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS (P1 of plans/OWNER-HELP-SUGGESTIONS.md):
#   The owner was juggling THREE guest checkout roots (/root/gzippy,
#   /root/gzippy-bench, /tmp/gz-ft-src) and TWO corpus paths concurrently. That is
#   the "which-build-is-which" trap: a measure can read a STALE binary from a root
#   different than the one just rebuilt, silently invalidating a result. This file
#   PINS ONE of each so the parity wrapper and the owner can never disagree.
#
# RULE: rebuild and measure MUST use the same $GUEST_SRC. parity.sh enforces this.

# ---- double-hop access (the SHORTER, newer form; see plans/GUEST.md) ----------
GUEST=10.30.0.199           # the actual perf box (LXC guest behind the jump host)
GUEST_USER=root
JUMP=neurotic               # ssh jump host (ProxyJump) in front of the guest
# Canonical ssh invocation. ALWAYS ConnectTimeout-bounded so a dead hop cannot
# wedge the tool channel (the "no wedged channel" rule). Use as: $SSH_GUEST "cmd"
SSH_GUEST="ssh -o ConnectTimeout=15 -J ${JUMP} ${GUEST_USER}@${GUEST}"
SSH_JUMP="ssh -o ConnectTimeout=15 ${JUMP}"

# ---- the ONE canonical checkout root (the pin) -------------------------------
# Chosen: /root/gzippy-bench — it is where host_lock_and_bench.sh and the existing
# guest_*.sh drivers already stage, so banked numbers and tooling agree. Both the
# build step and the measure step in parity.sh read ONLY this root.
# RE-PINNED 2026-06-15: the old /root/gzippy-bench root is GONE. The subject is a
# CLEAN worktree of gzippy at b22e1b14 built --no-default-features
# --features pure-rust-inflate, RUSTFLAGS="-C target-cpu=native". Source lives on
# /mnt/internal (823G free; / is only 8.4G), target built into /dev/shm for speed;
# the release binary is the load-bearing artifact. Assert GZIPPY_DEBUG=1 ->
# path=ParallelSM and run with GZIPPY_FORCE_PARALLEL_SM=1.
GUEST_ROOT=/mnt/internal/gz-b22
GUEST_SRC=${GUEST_ROOT}              # repo root on the guest (decide.sh scp target)
GZIPPY_BIN=/dev/shm/gz-b22-target/release/gzippy   # the pinned subject binary

# ---- pinned corpus (P3) -----------------------------------------------------
# The ONE corpus the parity wrapper reads. ensure-corpus.sh verifies size+sha and
# regenerates from the canonical source if absent/mismatched.
CORPUS=/root/silesia.gz
# Pinned identity of $CORPUS. The DECOMPRESSED sha is the load-bearing one — it is
# the correctness oracle every measured run is sha-verified against (Rule 4).
# Value supplied by the campaign spec (decompressed silesia-large payload).
CORPUS_RAW_SHA256=028bd002c89c9a909ccdbc2af0a223de285348edb014ccc8e27d297f52cb410f
# The compressed-file sha/size are filled by ensure-corpus.sh on first pin; leave
# blank to skip the compressed-file identity check (raw sha still enforced).
CORPUS_GZ_SHA256=
CORPUS_GZ_BYTES=
# Canonical regeneration source (per MEMORY: the squishy corpus). ensure-corpus.sh
# fetches+gzips from here only if $CORPUS is absent or fails its sha.
CORPUS_SRC_URL=https://jackdanger.com/squishy/silesia.tar

# ---- host-lock convention (Rule 6: frozen host) -----------------------------
# CPU pin mask for T8 (the campaign's primary parity cell): even cores, no SMT
# sibling contention. parity.sh derives other T from pin_mask().
TASKSET=0,2,4,6,8,10,12,14
GOV=performance             # required scaling governor (readback-asserted)
NO_TURBO=1                  # intel_pstate/no_turbo expected value (freq-pinned)

# ---- comparison target ------------------------------------------------------
# Native vendor build of rapidgzip — the HONEST bar. The pip wheel pays ~43ms
# Python startup per invocation (measured: --version wall 47-48ms); the native
# ELF takes 3-4ms. All banked numbers MUST use the native ELF or the ratios are
# inflated by ~43ms of unreachable startup tax.
#
# Provenance:
#   path: /root/gzippy-p35/vendor/rapidgzip/librapidarchive/build/src/tools/rapidgzip
#   sha256: b0397fca1bb1fd5f214a01c0b2f1fb3d8366279dd922920fca27a353ed1a9b49
#   version: rapidgzip 0.16.0
#   --version wall: 3ms (< 15ms threshold ⇒ native, not wheel)
#   built from: vendor/rapidgzip checkout in /root/gzippy-p35 via cmake
#
# If this path is absent on a fresh guest, rebuild:
#   cd /root/gzippy-p35/vendor/rapidgzip/librapidarchive && mkdir -p build && cd build
#   cmake .. -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release && make -j$(nproc) rapidgzip
# RE-PINNED 2026-06-15: /root/gzippy-p35 is GONE. Live native ELF (rapidgzip
# 0.16.0, --version wall ~0ms ⇒ native not the pip wheel):
RG_BIN=/root/oracle_c/rapidgzip-native
RG_BIN_SHA=
# Primary comparator — the native ELF. Scripts read $RG for the comparison arm.
RG=${RG_BIN}
# Pip-wheel arm — kept for continuity / tax-delta labeling (RG_WHEEL_BIN=... to
# enable the labeled wheel arm in a three-way interleave). Startup: ~48ms.
RG_WHEEL_BIN=/usr/local/bin/rapidgzip
# Trace build (used by oracle/fulcrum drivers — NOT the parity comparator).
RG_TRACE=${GUEST_SRC}/vendor/rapidgzip/librapidarchive/build-trace/src/tools/rapidgzip

# ---- comparator champion field (gzippy = SUBJECT, ranked vs EACH) ------------
# decide.sh adds an arm per present tool beside rapidgzip so the matrix ranks
# gzippy-native against the FASTEST tool on the box, not only rg. All arms sink
# to the SAME regular-file class as gz/rg (no sink asymmetry), are sha-verified,
# and self-validate via a per-tool A/A (binary-vs-itself ≈ 1.0). A tool absent on
# the guest is recorded (comp_absent=) and skipped — it never breaks gz<->rg.
# Inventory 2026-06-15 (guest 10.30.0.199, one read-only ssh):
#   libdeflate-gunzip /usr/bin/libdeflate-gunzip  (CLI has no --version)
#   igzip             /usr/bin/igzip              (igzip CLI 2.31.1, ISA-L)
#   pigz              /usr/bin/pigz               (pigz 2.8)
#   zlib-ng minigzip  ABSENT (no minigzip/minideflate in PATH or /usr/bin)
COMP_LIBDEFLATE=/usr/bin/libdeflate-gunzip   # single-shot C champion
COMP_IGZIP=/usr/bin/igzip                    # ISA-L single-shot champion
COMP_PIGZ=/usr/bin/pigz                      # parallel champion (-p <T>)
# zlib-ng minigzip is not installed; leave unset to skip. To enable, build it:
#   git clone https://github.com/zlib-ng/zlib-ng /root/zlib-ng
#   cd /root/zlib-ng && cmake -B build -DZLIB_COMPAT=ON -DWITH_GTEST=OFF \
#       -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release && cmake --build build -j$(nproc)
#   # minigzip / minideflate land in /root/zlib-ng/build/  then:
#   COMP_ZLIBNG=/root/zlib-ng/build/minigzip   (uses stdin: -d < file)
COMP_ZLIBNG=

# ---- artifact / scratch locations -------------------------------------------
# /dev/shm is RAM (large, fast); / on the guest is tiny (~1G). Captures go to shm.
ARTDIR_BASE=/dev/shm/gzippy-bench-art
FULCRUM=/tmp/fulcrum

# ---- build invariants (Rule 6: assert the production path) -------------------
RUSTFLAGS_PIN="-C target-cpu=native"
# gzippy-native is the SOLE production decode path (C-FFI off the decode graph).
# pure-rust-inflate is the legacy feature name; both build the pure-Rust engine.
DEFAULT_FEATURE=gzippy-native
